One of my clients who had been
at Enron,

00:07:20.269 --> 00:07:21.810
I became an
investment--conventional

00:07:21.810 --> 00:07:25.898
investment banking--
I became a consultant to Enron,

00:07:25.898 --> 00:07:30.728
started working on their
attempt to roll up their

00:07:30.728 --> 00:07:36.639
aggregate into one legal entity,
all of their foreign projects.

00:07:36.639 --> 00:07:42.053
After a while the complexities
were such that virtually no one

00:07:42.053 --> 00:07:47.288
had the institutional memory
required to be able to complete

00:07:47.288 --> 00:07:52.613
the deal except for one or two
people and they needed someone

00:07:52.613 --> 00:07:56.531
who knew what their--
knew the story to be able to

00:07:56.531 --> 00:08:01.497
really stay on with the company,
and they asked me if I wanted

00:08:01.497 --> 00:08:05.370
to do that and I ended up
agreeing.

00:08:05.370 --> 00:08:09.810
Then I was there a full nine
months until--

00:08:09.810 --> 00:08:13.363
this was in 1994,
I was there about nine months

00:08:13.363 --> 00:08:15.524
before I,
the general counsel and the

00:08:15.524 --> 00:08:18.730
controller,
all resigned in the fall of

00:08:18.730 --> 00:08:19.310
1995.
 

